<p>CSS or Cascading Styling Sheets applies fonts, colors, formatting, layout, etc. to your HTML elements. .</p>

<p>You use CSS by attaching a stylesheet to your page. Stylesheets look like this</p>

<div class="code_block">
<%= "<head>" %>
<%= "<style>" %>
.classy_class
{
background-color:red;
}
#my_favorite_div
{
font-height:200%;
}
<%= "</style>" %>
<%= "</head>" %>
</div>

<p>This will make the elements with class="classy_class" red, and double the height of the header h1. Notice that classes are represented by <b>periods</b>, and idâ€™s by <b>hashtags</b>.</p>

<p>You can also include a stylesheet as its own file</p>
<div class="code_block">
<%= '<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">' %>
</div>